originalText.text:
First I must say that Doctor Marano,
is the most awesome, professional, friendly, and knowledgeable
Surgeon. When it comes to the transgender community.
With a staff of wonderful and hard-working people especially Jill!
I have been lucky enough that today has been a month.
Since my breast augmentation surgery with Doctor Marano.
I had two other augmentation surgery with other doctors. Prior to Doctor Marano, which turned out to be a nightmare.
They had been doctors that were not educated when it comes to the transgender community and the transgender body. Unfortunately at the time that was the only option available to me. It had been so hard for me to find a Doctor in the East Coast. That was familiar with the trans body. and understood the trans body when it comes to medical procedures and body dysmorphia.
When I found out about Doctor Marano.
From day one I knew that I wanted him to perform my surgery.
Dr. Marano is young with so many fresh ideas whoâ€™s also a great listener. He knew that I had issues with surgery before. But I needed to correct my dysmorphia. He did an amazing job. I canâ€™t put into words how heâ€™s changed my life, and made me a more confident and happier person. I will be forever grateful to him. And I hope he understands what a blessing he has been in my life.
For Doctor Marano to have chosen the path of helping the trans community through surgeries. And for understanding how important.
It is for us to have Doctorâ€™s that work in our favor and not against us.
I have other procedures that I plan on getting done to help alleviate my dysmorphia issues.
Hope that
Doctor Marano will be able to perform them.
I trust him 100% with anything I will get done in the near future. So should you!
The staff here is accommodating, friendly, warming, engaging, good listeners, attentive and above all theyâ€™re here to help us and not judge us.
Thank you for everything guys!
Yours truly
Puerto Rican Diva
